This paper discusses edge caching in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes a deep actor-critic reinforcement learning-based multi-agent framework, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves dynamic control problems, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The proposed framework is based on reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses caching algorithms, which can be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
